# dotfiles

Personal shell, editor, and tool configuration.
Tools are provided by [dotpack](https://github.com/stefanpenner/dotpack) — a hermetic, statically-linked bundle.

## Bootstrap (new machine)

```sh
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/stefanpenner/dotfiles/master/bootstrap.sh | sh
```

Or step by step:

```sh
# 1. Install tools
curl -fsSL https://github.com/stefanpenner/dotpack/releases/latest/download/install.sh | bash
source ~/.profile

# 2. Clone and link config
git clone https://github.com/stefanpenner/dotfiles.git ~/src/stefanpenner/dotfiles
~/src/stefanpenner/dotfiles/sync.sh
```

## What's included

### Tools (via dotpack → `~/.local/`)
zsh, git, nvim, go, fzf, fd, bat, batman, rg, lsd, delta, jq, direnv, lazygit, htop,
plus zsh plugins (autosuggestions, fast-syntax-highlighting, history-substring-search, powerlevel10k).

### Config (this repo → symlinked to `~/`)
- `.zshrc` — machine-specific shell config, sources shared config from `.config/zsh/rc.zsh`
- `.config/zsh/rc.zsh` — portable zsh config (works with dotpack or brew)
- `.config/nvim/` — Neovim (LazyVim)
- `.gitconfig` — git config with delta pager
- `.p10k.zsh` — Powerlevel10k prompt theme
- `.tmux.conf` — tmux

## Updating

```sh
dotpack upgrade        # update tools
cd ~/src/stefanpenner/dotfiles && git pull && ./sync.sh   # update config
```

## Structure

```
~/.local/              ← dotpack (tools, plugins, binaries)
~/src/.../dotfiles/    ← this repo (config files)
  .zshrc              ← machine-specific
  .config/zsh/rc.zsh  ← shared/portable
  .config/nvim/       ← editor
  sync.sh             ← symlinks dotfiles to ~/
  bootstrap.sh        ← full setup from scratch
```
